(35, 43, 'en', 'Competitive Analysis', 'Competitive Analysis', '<h1>Competitive Analysis<br><br><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/PoBZsXGHJfg\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></h1><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>When doing&nbsp;<strong>competitive analysis</strong>, you can compare&nbsp;<em>features</em>&nbsp;and you can compare&nbsp;<em>experiences</em>.</p> <p>For&nbsp;<strong>feature comparison</strong>, what you would do is select a list of core features, and then see how each feature works on the competing site.</p> <p>For&nbsp;<strong>experience comparison</strong>, you might take the following steps:</p> <ol><li>Survey users about their experience with competitors</li><li>Identify what users care about (e.g., users really value “customization” or “finding deals”)</li><li>Understand users’ experience with competitors</li><li>Select metrics (e.g., usability, customization, etc.)</li><li>Rate each competitor against the metrics</li><li>Summarize\r\n your learnings. (e.g., Users rate product A very high on usability \r\nbecause product A simplified the purchasing process. Our product should \r\nlearn from product A).</li></ol> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2>There are many kinds of competitive analysis</h2> <p>There are many different ways to do&nbsp;<strong>competitive analysis</strong>, and many different questions you may want to focus on. For example:</p> <ul><li>Are you interested in learning more about what services your competitors offer?</li><li>Are you interested in a deep-dive on the interaction design?</li><li>Do you want to learn more about how users perceive the competing products?</li></ul> <p>You can look at direct competitors, indirect competitors, partial competitors, or even analogous competitors.</p> <p>If you\'d like to dive deeper into this topic, I recommend this article about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.palantir.net/blog/competitive-analysis-budget\" target=\"_blank\">Competitive Analysis on a Budget</a>.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153)\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Course\r\n content is sourced from Udacity, a third-party online learning platform\r\n and other online sources. We do not own the right to this content.</span></em></span></p> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p></p><p></p>'),
(36, 44, 'en', 'Design with Data in Mind', 'Design with Data in Mind', '<p><span class=\"z-fw:700 z-fs:17\"></span>    </p><div class=\"zls-header-right z-dis:flex-al-c z-gap:10\">  </div>      <ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h1>Design with Data in Mind</h1> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/7-8zFDGzeGc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Remember,\r\n competitive analysis can be super useful, but it\'s not a good idea to \r\nsimply copy what your competitors are doing. You don\'t know what (if \r\nany) data they based a design decision on. What\'s more, you may be \r\ntargeting different users with your product. In the end, you\'ll need \r\nyour own data on&nbsp;<em>your</em>&nbsp;target users.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Many\r\n of today\'s successful companies take a data-driven approach to creating\r\n their products. When you look at any popular product (for example, \r\nshoes at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.zappos.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Zappos.com</a>),\r\n everything you see on the screen—from the hex value of the blue \r\npromotion banner to the name of the button—is probably backed by data.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div> <div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ewtpm4\"> <div class=\"css-10jk0gc\">  <div class=\"css-1bdyswo\"> <div class=\"css-1aq2jbx\"> <div class=\"chakra-container css-1es7f9a\"> <div class=\"css-pr2tx6\"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>Just\r\n to give you an idea of the kinds of data-related questions you might \r\nask, here are some you could apply to the HotelFinder example:</p> <ul><li>What data do I have right now? (e.g., \"we collect historical data on the price of a hotel\")</li><li>Which\r\n data do my users care about? (e.g., \"our users always search for \r\ndeals—so they want to know whether a hotel is lower than usual price\")</li><li>If\r\n I decide to show the historical pricing data for hotels to our users, \r\nhow will this impact their behavior? (Will this cause users who have \r\npreviously booked hotels to ask for a refund if they now can see they \r\ndidn’t book their hotels at a good price?)</li><li>Why do lots of users\r\n not make it through the user journey? (e.g., \"why do 60% of our users \r\nabandon our site when we ask them to enter their credit card?\")</li></ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>So\r\n it\'s important to design with data in mind. But how do we get that \r\ndata? In the next lesson, we\'ll look at some ways to get data about our \r\nusers through interviews and surveys.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"chakra-stack css-sy0k4m\">&nbsp;</div> </div> </div> </div>  </div> </div> </div> <div>&nbsp;</div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153)\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Course\r\n content is sourced from Udacity, a third-party online learning platform\r\n and other online sources. We do not own the right to this content.</span></em></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li></ul>           <p></p>'),
(37, 45, 'en', 'Review', 'Review', '<h1>Review</h1><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/aZPevfzZBQQ\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>In this lesson, we took a tour through many of the fundamentals you need to have in mind before starting your research:</p> <ul><li>We asked the question,&nbsp;<strong>what is good UX?</strong>&nbsp;And\r\n we looked at a number of examples of different products and interfaces,\r\n while considering what might make them good (or bad) experiences for \r\nusers.</li><li>We went over&nbsp;<strong>Nielsen\'s 10 heuristics</strong>&nbsp;and saw how we can use heuristics to quickly and inexpensively evaluate a design.</li><li>We looked at how and when to do&nbsp;<strong>competitive analysis</strong>.</li><li>We talked about the importance of&nbsp;<strong>designing with users in mind</strong>&nbsp;and to&nbsp;<strong>designing with data in mind</strong>.</li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Although\r\n we talked a little about research and data in this lesson, we didn\'t \r\nget into many specifics. In the next lesson, we\'ll discuss UX research \r\nin more detail, and you\'ll get started on the research for your project.</p> <p>By now, you should have&nbsp;<strong>selected the design topic for your final project</strong>.\r\n If you haven\'t settled on a topic yet, you\'ll want to do that now, \r\nsince you\'ll be doing research on that topic in the next lesson.<span></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153)\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Course\r\n content is sourced from Udacity, a third-party online learning platform\r\n and other online sources. We do not own the right to this content.</span></em></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li></ul>         <div id=\"popup-container\" class=\"zw-main-container\" style=\"display: block;\"><div class=\"zw-flex zw-fl-normal zw-fl-grow zls-overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"zls-right-col zw-flex zw-flex-column zw-fl-normal zw-fl-grow zls-overflow-hidden\" id=\"lesson-container\">         </div> </div>       </div>\r\n<div id=\"zw-searchResultsWrap\"></div> \r\n  <div id=\"lyte-components-div\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<template class=\"zw-block {{if(isBlankSlate,\'zls-stop-animation\')}} {{tableClass}}\">    </template>\r\n\r\n\r\n<template class=\"zls-iframe-wrapper zls-document-element {{if(showNativeFullscreen,\'zw-pos-re\')}}\">  </template>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div><div class=\"popoverWrapper\"> <div class=\"lytePopover\" style=\"height: auto; width: auto; transition-duration: 0.2s; opacity: 0;\"> <span id=\"lytePopoverArrow\" class=\"lytePopoverArrowIcon\"></span><br></div></div><p></p><p></p>'),
(38, 46, 'en', 'Lesson Overview', 'Lesson Overview', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h1>Lesson Overview</h1><h1><span><br></span></h1><h1><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/H_ivez0f5eo\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><span><br></span></h1><h1><span><br></span></h1><p>In this lesson, we\'ll be looking at key components of the UX research process, including:</p> <ul><li>How to create a research plan</li><li>How to recruit participants</li><li>How to conduct a semi-structured interview study</li><li>How to conduct a survey study, including how to ask effective survey questions</li><li>How to analyze data</li><li>How to create a report</li></ul><h1></h1><h1><span><br></span></h1><h1><span><br></span></h1> </div>   </div>'),
(39, 47, 'en', 'Taking Advantage of Existing Data', 'Taking Advantage of Existing Data', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h1>Taking Advantage of Existing Data</h1><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/3zGN9SlHfdE\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2>Stakeholder interviews</h2> <p>In\r\n the video just now, we only briefly discussed stakeholder \r\ninterviews—let\'s look at them in a little more detail, and then go over a\r\n concrete example.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3>Who are the stakeholders?</h3> <p>Stakeholders\r\n are simply the people who play a role in the project. Stakeholders can \r\nbe business leads, product managers, engineers, project managers and \r\nmany others.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3>Why should we conduct stakeholder interviews?</h3> <p>Asking\r\n the right questions can help the UX team understand what stakeholders \r\nare trying to achieve and plan the UX resources accordingly. \r\nSpecifically, we want:</p> <ul><li>To understand what stakeholders want</li><li>To understand what types of outcomes stakeholders expect</li><li>To understand where stakeholders see UX fitting into the project</li><li>To align goals with stakeholders and avoid misunderstanding</li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3>Questions to ask early on</h3> <p>When we are in the early stages of a project, here are the general kinds of things we want to find out from stakeholders:</p> <ul><li><strong>Why</strong>&nbsp;do we want to build this feature?</li><li><strong>What</strong>&nbsp;do we already know?</li><li><strong>How</strong>&nbsp;do we define success?<span></span></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p><strong>To learn more about the project background</strong><br>How\r\n did you decide to prioritize this project? Who are the primary users? \r\nWhat do you want to provide to the users? Are there any other key \r\nstakeholders we should talk to?</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p><strong>Existing work and data</strong><br>Has\r\n our team done any similar projects before? What parallel efforts are \r\nyou aware of (are there any other teams doing similar things)? What \r\ntypes of data are we currently collecting? What types of UX research \r\nhave we done? What are the key learnings?<span></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p><strong>Collaboration</strong><br>What\r\n is the timeline? What are the milestones? How much do you want to be \r\ninvolved in the UX process? How often should we sync up on progress?</p> </div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p><p><br></p> </div>   </div>'),
(40, 48, 'en', 'UX Research 101', 'UX Research 101', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h1>UX Research 101</h1><h2>Quantitative Studies</h2><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/HBRsoC6Sp1g\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>The key things to remember with&nbsp;<strong>quantitative</strong>&nbsp;studies are that they typically involve collecting data from a&nbsp;<em>large number of users</em>, usually through surveys or other tools that can be administered at scale—and, in the end, the results you end up with involve&nbsp;<em>numerical data</em>&nbsp;(e.g.,\r\n \"70% of users click on the blue button more than the green button\"). \r\nNotice that data like this often doesn\'t tell us the underlying reasons&nbsp;<em>why</em>&nbsp;(e.g., we do not know&nbsp;<em>why</em>&nbsp;users are clicking on the one button more than the other).<span></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2>Qualitative Studies</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/g2lhrkJr9C8\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The key things to remember about&nbsp;<strong>qualitative studies</strong>&nbsp;are that they typically involve having&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">in-depth interactions</em>&nbsp;with a&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">small number of users</em>—and because you are having such in-depth interactions, you are able to probe the underlying reasons&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">why</em>&nbsp;the user does something, as well as the specifics of&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">how</em> they do it.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Quantitative vs. Qualitative</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/_PeZvq-vxbg\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Let\'s briefly summarize the key characteristics of quantitative and qualitative studies:</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><strong>Quantitative studies</strong></p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Large sample sizes</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Understand the preferences, behaviors and attitudes of the general population</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Result in numerical data (e.g.. \"70% of users click on the green button\")</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">For example: surveys, A/B testing, card sorting, or other tools that can be administered at scale</li></ul> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><strong>Qualitative studies</strong></p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Small sample sizes</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">In-depth interactions</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Allow researchers to probe why and how</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">For example: interviews,&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contextual_inquiry\" target=\"_blank\">contextual inquiry</a>, participatory design,&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concept_testing\" target=\"_blank\">concept testing</a>, etc.</li></ul> Note\r\n that some research methods can be done in both qualitative and \r\nquantitative ways—for example, diary studies and usability studies. \r\nLet\'s consider an example of a usability study and talk about what kind \r\nof information a qualitative study would give us, and then compare this \r\nwith the kind of data we would get from a quantitative study.</div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/t7HaF3xP8Nw\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p><p></p> </div>   </div>'),
(41, 49, 'en', 'Let\'s Research!', 'Let\'s Research!', '<ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\"><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\"><div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 11, 11)\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\" style=\"\"><div class=\"copy-length css-0\" style=\"\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\" style=\"\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\" style=\"\">By\r\n now, you should have a UX topic in mind for your final project, so it\'s\r\n time to start making concrete plans for how to plan your research. \r\nWe\'ll spend most of the rest of this lesson going over the main steps \r\nthat you\'ll typically see in a UX study:</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 11, 11)\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\" style=\"\">&nbsp;</div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000035181&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000035181\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">In this next video, we\'ll go over all five of these steps briefly, and then we\'ll zoom in on step 1—<strong>creating a research plan</strong>.</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/dmM7jv1KJNQ\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">The Parts of a Research Plan</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">As we just saw, a typical UX research plan will have these components:</p> <ol class=\"css-13a5a39\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Background</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Research goals</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Research questions</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Recruiting</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Script</li></ol> Let\'s talk about each of these in more detail.</div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/nxBz61TKQio\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Screener survey for recruiting participants</h2> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <blockquote> <p>A screener (or&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">screening survey</em>)\r\n is a set of up to ~10 questions placed at the beginning of an actual \r\nsurvey to determine if a person is or isn\'t the right fit for a \r\nparticular study.<br>Those who qualify the screener should attempt the actual survey.<span></span></p> </blockquote> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">As\r\n I said in the video, you can send potential participants a screener \r\nsurvey to see if they have the characteristics you\'re looking for in \r\nyour target users. If you\'d like to get a better idea of what screeners \r\nare like, you can</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">fill out the&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://userresearch.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Google UX research screener</a>&nbsp;or</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">fill out one for the&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/usability/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Microsoft UX research screener</a>.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">refer to a&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/resources/guide-to-using-screening-questions/\" target=\"_blank\">guide to using screening questions in your survey</a><span></span></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>For\r\n your own screener, it does not need to be as comprehensive as these \r\nexamples. You can create your own screener using an online survey tool \r\nlike&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.google.com/forms/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Google Forms</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Survey Monkey</a>.\r\n If you are recruiting families and friends to be the free participants \r\nfor your very first UX research project, you don’t have to have a \r\nscreener.</p> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"></p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><br></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(42, 50, 'en', 'How to conduct a Semi-Structured interviews', 'How to conduct a Semi-Structured interviews', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/E6WNZXq083E\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/kvbUsskGxaU\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Writing\r\n good interview questions can be challenging. For your reference, here\'s\r\n a downloadable PDF that has all the tips we just went over, along with \r\nadditional examples:</p> <ul><li><a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/October/5da4cfc9_uxnd-reference-sheet-tips-for-interview-questions/uxnd-reference-sheet-tips-for-interview-questions.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tips for Interview Questions</a><span></span></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2>Follow-up questions</h2> <p>Note\r\n that you can—and will often want to—have multiple interview questions \r\nthat all get at the same underlying research question. This allows you \r\nto follow a line of questioning that makes sense for each user.</p> <p><strong>Research question:</strong><br>[User behaviors] How do language learners currently study languages?</p> <p><strong>Interview question:</strong><br>You\r\n mentioned earlier that you are currently using Duolingo. What time of \r\nday and where do you usually use Duolingo? [Does participant have a \r\ndaily routine? Is it spontaneous?]</p> <p><strong>Follow-up questions:</strong></p> <ul><li>Ask\r\n participants about the context [when and where]: At noon every day? Are\r\n they on a short lunch break? When they are waiting for a bus?</li><li>Ask participants why they choose to use the app in certain locations or during certain times</li></ul> <h2>Additional reading</h2> <p>If\r\n you\'d like to look deeper into semi-structured interviews, you can find\r\n some great tips (written for beginning researchers) in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://uhra.herts.ac.uk/bitstream/handle/2299/7736/Appendix%206.pdf?sequence=11\" target=\"_blank\">this article</a></p></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(43, 51, 'en', 'Write interview questions', 'Write interview questions', '<p>Previously, you created your research plan—but it\'s not really \r\ncomplete yet, because it doesn\'t have your actual interview questions. \r\nSo now it’s time to write the interview questions for your own study, \r\nand add them to your research plan.</p> <p>Each interview question \r\nshould be clearly related to an underlying research question, and you \r\nshould provide a rationale to explain why the question is being \r\nincluded.</p> <p>Writing good interview questions can be challenging! As you work on them, you\'ll probably want to reference the previous page (<strong>How to do Semi-Structured Interviews</strong>) or the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/October/5da4cfc9_uxnd-reference-sheet-tips-for-interview-questions/uxnd-reference-sheet-tips-for-interview-questions.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tips for Interview Questions PDF</a>. It\'ll probably be especially helpful to look at the example questions (both good and bad).</p> It may also help to refer to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/October/5da657d1_example-research-plan/example-research-plan.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">example research plan</a>&nbsp;that we provided earlier—you\'ll see there are interview questions there, along with a rationale for each question.<p></p>'),
(44, 52, 'en', 'Recruit Participants', 'Recruit Participants', '<ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>Once you have your research plan worked out, it\'s time to start on the next step—recruiting participants!</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000026001&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000026001\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\">  <div class=\"css-1mnskd6\"> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>The life cycle of a UX research study—here, we are talking about step 2: recruiting participants</p> </div> </div>  </div> </div> </div>   </div>  </div><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Ug-vLXAk_qI\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></div><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\"><br></div><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\"><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Scheduling\r\n interviews and conducting the actual interviews takes some time. For \r\nyour own project, I’d encourage you to start recruiting early.</p> <p>For the final project, you will need to interview a minimum of&nbsp;<strong>two participants</strong>.\r\n But be aware that you are not likely to get the best data from only \r\ntalking with two people. There isn’t a magic number for how many users \r\nyou need to talk to, but if you have time, I recommend that you try for \r\nat least&nbsp;<strong>five participants</strong>. After you talk to a few \r\nusers, you will probably start to notice themes and patterns in their \r\nanswers. Some people will probably have similar needs or pain points.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153)\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Course\r\n content is sourced from Udacity, a third-party online learning platform\r\n and other online sources. We do not own the right to this content.</span></em></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li></ul>           </div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(45, 53, 'en', 'Run the study', 'Run the study', '<p>Once you\'ve got a plan and have recruited your participants, it\'s time \r\nto actually run your interviews and collect data from your users.</p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/1qi3jbPG7qc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Now\r\n that you have your research plan and you\'ve recruited some \r\nparticipants, it\'s time to actually run your interviews. Be sure to take\r\n notes during your interviews.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <blockquote> <p>Note:\r\n Once you\'ve finished your interviews and have your data in hand, we\'ll \r\nlook at how to organize and analyze that data. It may help to look ahead\r\n to the next page to get an idea of what that will look like, so you \r\nknow how you\'ll be using the data you collect.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p></p>');
INSERT INTO `text_lesson_translations` (`id`, `text_lesson_id`, `locale`, `title`, `summary`, `content`) VALUES
(46, 54, 'en', 'Analyze Data (Affinity Mapping)', 'Analyze Data (Affinity Mapping)', '<p>Once you\'ve run your study, you\'ll probably have a mountain of data. So \r\nin the next step, we\'ll work on organizing and analyzing that data. \r\nLet\'s look at how we can use something called&nbsp;<strong>affinity diagramming</strong> to help use do this.</p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/t-Q8VxX5ByY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>I created my digital affinity diagram using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://miro.com/\" target=\"_blank\">miro.com</a>.\r\n If you prefer, you can use Post-Its to create a physical affinity \r\ndiagram (Post-It also has an app!) or use other digital tools. After you\r\n are done, take a photo or screenshot of your affinity diagram, to \r\ninclude in your research report.</p> <p>It requires patience to \r\nsummarize notes and create an affinity diagram. If you can’t find a fit \r\nfor a note, just put it to the side and find a place for it later. There\r\n isn’t a perfect way to create an affinity diagram. The important thing \r\nis whether the affinity diagram helps you discover key insights.</p> <p>Ultimately,\r\n your goal is to use the affinity diagram to identify any patterns or \r\nkey findings that exist in the data. When you do the affinity diagram \r\nfor your study, ask yourself, what interesting insights are there in the\r\n data? Whether a particular piece of data counts as an interesting \r\ninsight takes some judgment and depends on the context. For example, if \r\nall participants say, “I watch YouTube everyday”, this is probably not a\r\n very interesting insight if you are talking about college students \r\nliving in Boston. But if your interviewees are grandfathers living in \r\nrural Laos, that could be an interesting finding.<span></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000025007&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000025007\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\">  <div class=\"css-1mnskd6\"> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>Facing\r\n issues while viewing the font above? You can download the same image \r\nfrom the bottom of this page. Right-click on the file name, and choose \r\nthe&nbsp;<em>Save As...</em>&nbsp;option.</p> </div> </div>  </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"css-1dtn3on\"> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \">&nbsp;</div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-k008qs\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Once you have run your interviews and have all your notes, it\'s time to create your own affinity diagram!</p> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <ol class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-list zls-blocks-list-numbers\"><li> <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Take your interview data and transfer it into the format we showed above (notes with short summaries on them).&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://miro.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Miro</a> is a great tool for this, but you can use whatever format you prefer.</p> </div> </div> </li><li> <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Be\r\n sure each note has enough information to understand it by itself (so \r\nthat you don\'t get confused by your own notes if you look at them again \r\nlater).</p> </div> </li><li> <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Group the notes by themes.</p> </div> </li><li> <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>If applicable, group the themes into higher-level themes.</p> </div> </li><li> <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Take a photo or screenshot of your affinity diagram (so you can include it in your report—which we\'ll look at next).</p> </div> </li></ol>   </div> </li></ul>         <div id=\"popup-container\" class=\"zw-main-container\" style=\"display: block;\"><div class=\"zw-flex zw-fl-normal zw-fl-grow zls-overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"zls-right-col zw-flex zw-flex-column zw-fl-normal zw-fl-grow zls-overflow-hidden\" id=\"lesson-container\">         </div> </div>       </div>\r\n<div id=\"zw-searchResultsWrap\"></div> \r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"lyte-components-div\"><template class=\"zw-block {{if(isBlankSlate,\'zls-stop-animation\')}} {{tableClass}}\">    </template>\r\n\r\n\r\n<template class=\"zls-iframe-wrapper zls-document-element {{if(showNativeFullscreen,\'zw-pos-re\')}}\">  </template></div><p></p><p><br></p>'),
(47, 55, 'en', 'Share Your Results', 'Share Your Results', '<ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>Once\r\n you\'ve collected and organized the insights from your research, it\'s \r\ntime to socialize your findings—that is, to share them with others. If \r\nyou are working as a professional UX designer, this can be an important \r\nstep for getting buy-in from the other stakeholders at your company.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\">&nbsp;</div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000023177&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000023177\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2>The Research Report</h2> <p>A common way to share findings from a UX study is to summarize them in a&nbsp;<strong>research report</strong>, so that others can easily see the key results of your work.</p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/K0xvAaYrYGc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/d5_UpQeNhPM\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <blockquote> <p><strong>Tips:</strong>\r\n The key is to make the report digestible. Remember, stakeholders&nbsp;won\'t \r\nbe familiar with the research you have been working on, but they should \r\nbe able to understand it by reading your report.</p> <p>If your research\r\n includes artifacts (photos you take during the interview), you should \r\ninclude them in the report to help readers understand what you are \r\ntalking about.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div>  </div></div></div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(48, 56, 'en', 'Plan Survey Study', 'Plan Survey Study', '<ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Once\r\n you\'ve gathered findings from your interviews, it\'s often a good idea \r\nto follow up with a survey study. Remember, one reason for this is to \r\nask if the results you found with the small number of people you \r\ninterviewed will apply to the larger population.</p> <p>Rather than \r\ntrying to investigate everything you learned in your interviews, you \r\nshould take the opportunity to narrow down the scope of your study and \r\njust select one or two key findings that you\'d like to check into \r\nfurther with your surveys.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <blockquote> <p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;In this section, we\'ll walk you through how to both&nbsp;<strong>plan</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>run</strong>&nbsp;your\r\n survey. For your own project, we only require you to demonstrate that \r\nyou know how to do the first of these two steps—to plan the survey and \r\nwrite questions for it. You can then go ahead and run the survey if you \r\nhave time, but this is an optional step that isn\'t required for your \r\nproject.</p></blockquote><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/f7QlNMzStTA\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><h2>Tips for Creating Effective Surveys</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/PtXIBXMnAu0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>You can download a reference sheet with these tips here <span></span>:</p> <ul><li><a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/October/5da62ed7_uxnd-reference-sheet-tips-for-survey-questions/uxnd-reference-sheet-tips-for-survey-questions.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tips for Survey Questions</a></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <h2>Running the Survey and Presenting the Data</h2><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/GeXbyDwW5ls\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-671zrp\">Plan your survey study</h3> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>It\'s\r\n time to think about your own survey study. Like with your interview \r\nstudy, you should first plan out your survey before you run it.</p> <p>So\r\n the first step is to go back to your research plan document and add a \r\nnew section for your survey study. As before, you may want to look at \r\nthe&nbsp;<a href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/October/5da657d1_example-research-plan/example-research-plan.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">example research plan</a>—you\'ll find an example for a survey study under the heading&nbsp;<strong>Study 2: Survey</strong>.</p> <p>Remember,\r\n your goal with the survey study is to follow up on a few of the key \r\nfindings from your interview study, in order to explore those ideas \r\nfurther and check whether they hold true for the larger population.</p> <p>Just like before, you should be sure to include the following in your plan:</p> </div> <div class=\"css-1pbf5mu\"><br> <ul class=\"css-1m3y3vl\"><li class=\"css-0\">The background for the study</li><li class=\"css-0\">The research goals</li><li class=\"css-0\">The overarching research questions</li><li class=\"css-0\">How and where you will recruit participants</li><li class=\"css-0\">The survey questions themselves</li><li class=\"css-0\">A rationale for each question</li></ul> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(49, 57, 'en', 'Addition Research Methods', 'Addition Research Methods', '<h3>Part I: Diary studies and card sorting</h3><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/75LoqA1iSBM\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><h3>Part II: Personas and Jobs-to-be-done</h3><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/AXOGJ81sF2I\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2>Additional resources</h2> <p>For\r\n your final project, you are free to conduct additional research \r\nstudies. (For UX research, it is always a matter of \"the more the \r\nmerrier\"!)</p> <p>Here are some additional readings to check out if you want to dive deeper into research methods:</p> <ul><li><a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/which-ux-research-methods/\" target=\"_blank\">When to use which user-experience research method</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.designkit.org/methods\" target=\"_blank\">IDEO.org design kit</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Universal-Methods-Design-Innovative-Effective/dp/1592537561\" target=\"_blank\">Universal Methods of Design</a><span></span></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <blockquote> <h4>Note</h4> <p>The persona shown above was created with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sketch.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sketch</a>. Persona photo credits: Photo by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@gregoryallen?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\" target=\"_blank\">Gregory Hayes</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/man\" target=\"_blank\">Unsplash</a>.</p></blockquote></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p>'),
(50, 58, 'en', 'Review', 'Review', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/UiO_F6Rll8Q\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p> </p><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div> <div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ewtpm4\"> <div class=\"css-10jk0gc\">  <div class=\"css-1bdyswo\"> <div class=\"css-1aq2jbx\"> <div class=\"chakra-container css-1es7f9a\"> <div class=\"css-pr2tx6\"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div> <div class=\"_15vzQlp3FJ8f94suLiPCPf ureact-markdown \"> <p>In this lesson, we looked at key components of the UX research process, including:</p> <ul><li>How to create a research plan</li><li>How to recruit participants</li><li>How to conduct a semi-structured interview study</li><li>How to conduct a survey study, including how to ask effective survey questions</li><li>How to analyze data</li><li>How to create a research report</li></ul> <p>If\r\n you followed along and did all of the above for your own study, then \r\nyou are very close to finishing the final project! The last component \r\nwill be to create a design sketch for part of your product. We\'ll look \r\nat that in the next lesson.<span></span></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>  </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div>'),
(51, 59, 'en', 'Thinking is hard', 'Thinking is hard', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">As\r\n humans, we may like to think of ourselves as \"the thinking animals\". \r\nBut thinking is hard! When we process information, try to understand \r\nwhat we\'re looking at, or make a choice about something—all of these \r\ntasks take time and energy.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Many \r\nhuman behaviors can be understood by keeping this in mind. As human \r\nbeings, our users have limited time and energy to think about what we\'re\r\n showing them. So if we want our product to give them a good experience,\r\n we need to design in a way that reduces this mental load.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">&nbsp;</p> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Text and readability</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/1Ena3GhxWZk\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Remember:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Users don\'t read; they scan</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Our job is to help users scan faster and get the information they need</li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Choices and past experiences</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/LmIfyUWjb1Q\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p> </p><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Remember:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><strong>Choice are good</strong>&nbsp;because they give the user autonomy and freedom, but&nbsp;<strong>too many choices can be overwhelming</strong>&nbsp;and may result in \"choice paralysis\".</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">A good way to save the user time and energy is to&nbsp;<strong>use existing patterns</strong>&nbsp;that\r\n they\'ve seen before. They know where to look for a particular feature \r\nbecause they\'ve seen that feature before in other apps. That said, we \r\nmay sometimes have good reasons for being creative and doing something \r\ndifferently. Violating expectations can sometimes (like when building a \r\ngame) be done in a positive way that is fun for the user. But we want to\r\n do this mindfully and make sure our users really do like it!</li></ul> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Further reading</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If this topic interests you, you might enjoy Steve Krug\'s classic (and very short) book on usability testing,&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"http://sensible.com/dmmt.html\" target=\"_blank\">Don\'t Make Me Think</a>.<span></span></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div>        </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p></p> </div>   </div>'),
(52, 60, 'en', 'Gestalt Principles', 'Gestalt Principles', '<p>German psychologists in the 1920s proposed theories around the \r\nperception in vision to explain how people organize visual information, \r\ncalled as&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/nmeth1110-863.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Gestalt principles</a>&nbsp;You can have a look at a brief overview&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"http://www.scholarpedia.org/article/Gestalt_principles?__hstc=77520074.36a0ddae8e24bce7\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/OFSmMgjMdFg\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Here is a summary of the key design psychology principles you should be taking away from this course:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Users don’t read; they scan.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Apply\r\n Gestalt principles in design; consider how the \"form\" (e.g., spacing \r\nand grouping) of your design affects the user experience.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Users like to have choices, but not too many choices.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Our peripheral vision is poor at seeing, but sensitive to motions.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Our past experience shapes our expectations.</li></ul> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If you\'d like to go deeper, here are some books I recommend:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books/about/Designing_with_the_Mind_in_Mind.html?id=woVADVwtL1gC&amp;source=kp_book_description\" target=\"_blank\">Designing with the Mind in Mind</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Things-Designer-People-Voices-Matter/dp/0321767535\" target=\"_blank\">100 Things Every Designer Needs to Know About People</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Dont-Make-Think-Revisited-Usability/dp/0321965515/ref=pd_bxgy_14_img_3/131-7452031-8962139?_encoding=UTF8&amp;pd_rd_i=0321965515&amp;pd_rd_r=3bccddd3-89b4-4735-9b3a-215f60876f40&amp;pd_rd_w=0iqZ4&amp;pd_rd_wg=S8ha1&amp;pf_rd_p=a2006322-0bc0-4db9-a08e-d168c18ce6f0&amp;pf_rd_r=7RF4A5ZJ3J3GBCKVNFF3&amp;psc=1&amp;refRID=7RF4A5ZJ3J3GBCKVNFF3\" target=\"_blank\">Don\'t Make Me Think</a></li></ul><p></p>'),
(53, 61, 'en', 'Emotional Design', 'Emotional Design', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/WNWcpFaAs04\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The vocabulary builder app gives quizzes to students. When a student fails a quiz, they see this page:<span></span></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000038523&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000038523\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">This is very discouraging to see a red \"fail\" on the screen.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Further reading</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">We mentioned designer&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://jnd.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Don Norman</a>&nbsp;earlier in this course. If you are interested in emotional design, you might want to check out his book by the same title:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/books/emotional-design/\" target=\"_blank\">Emotional Design by Don Norman</a><span></span></li></ul> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li></ul>           <p></p>'),
(54, 62, 'en', 'Improve Your Design', 'Improve Your Design', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/DtHtoKq-UFc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Earlier\r\n in this lesson you did a sketch for your project, making use of your \r\nresearch findings. Now that we\'ve talked about some common design \r\nprinciples, it\'s time to iterate on your sketch again—using what you\'ve \r\nlearned to make further improvements.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The goal is to select at least one design principle that you\'ve learned in this course and use it to make an improved sketch.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Below you can see my&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">before</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">after</em>&nbsp;sketches.\r\n In iteration 1, my design lists all the available vocabulary sets to \r\nusers. There can be more than dozens of sets, so that\'s a lot of \r\nchoices!<span></span></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000038525&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000038525\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Trying\r\n to decide which set to review could result in choice paralysis. So in \r\niteration 2, I reduced the number of choices down to 2: The user can \r\neither choose a recommended new set or review a recommended set they \r\nhave already seen. Users still get to choose whether they want to study \r\nsomething new or review, but they don’t need to choose from a huge list \r\nof sets.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Your goal is to do something similar, and then add notes explaining the improvements. You can have a look at my example&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/September/5d78390d_example-design-sketch/example-design-sketch.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">And for your reference, you can get a summary of the main design principles we\'ve covered in this lesson&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://video.udacity-data.com/topher/2019/October/5da62a69_uxnd-reference-sheet-design-principles/uxnd-reference-sheet-design-principles.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(55, 63, 'en', 'Review', 'Review', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/J-2o25U20hc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p> </p><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">You\'ve learned a&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">lot</em>&nbsp;in this course, including how to:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Use heuristics to quickly and inexpensively evaluate a design</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Design with users and data in mind</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Plan UX research studies</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Write interview and survey questions</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Screen, recruit, and run participants in your studies</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Write research reports</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Apply psychological principles to your design sketches</li></ul> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If you\'d like to go deeper into design principles and the psychology of design, here are some books I recommend:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books/about/Designing_with_the_Mind_in_Mind.html?id=woVADVwtL1gC&amp;source=kp_book_description\" target=\"_blank\">Designing with the Mind in Mind</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Things-Designer-People-Voices-Matter/dp/0321767535\" target=\"_blank\">100 Things Every Designer Needs to Know About People</a></li></ul> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Now it\'s time to demonstrate your new UX skills by completing and submitting your final project!</p> </div>   </div>   </div>'),
(56, 64, 'en', 'The basics of type & fonts in Figma', 'The basics of type & fonts in Figma', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/5i-ebNTjad8\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p>Typography is an essential aspect of UI/UX design. It helps communicate \r\nthe message of the design effectively and make the content more readable\r\n and attractive to the audience. In Figma, typography can be used to \r\ncreate headings, body text, buttons, and other UI elements.</p><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/axf__KqfP8M\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Here are some of the basics of type and fonts in Figma:</p> <p><strong>Choosing the Right Font</strong><br>Choosing\r\n the right font is an important step in creating effective UI/UX \r\ndesigns. There are two main types of fonts: Serif and Sans Serif. Serif \r\nfonts have small lines at the end of the letters, while Sans Serif fonts\r\n do not. Sans Serif fonts are generally considered more modern and \r\neasier to read, especially on digital screens.</p> <p><strong>Font Pairing</strong><br>When\r\n creating a design, it\'s important to choose fonts that work well \r\ntogether. Figma has a built-in font pairing feature that suggests \r\ncomplementary fonts based on the one you\'ve selected. You can also use \r\nonline tools to find font pairs that work well together.</p> <p><strong>Font Size and Hierarchy</strong><br>Font\r\n size and hierarchy are important aspects of typography. The font size \r\nshould be consistent across the design, and headings should be larger \r\nthan body text to create a clear visual hierarchy. Figma has a built-in \r\nfeature that allows you to set font size and line height, and adjust \r\nthem to create a hierarchy.</p> <p><strong>Font Weight and Style</strong><br>Font\r\n weight and style can also be used to create a hierarchy and add visual \r\ninterest to the design. Bold fonts can be used for headings, while \r\nlighter weights can be used for body text. You can also use italic or \r\nunderlined fonts to emphasize certain words or phrases.</p> <p><strong>Custom Fonts</strong><br>In\r\n addition to the built-in fonts in Figma, you can also import custom \r\nfonts. This can be useful if you want to use a brand-specific font or a \r\nfont that\'s not included in Figma\'s library.</p> </div>   </div>'),
(57, 65, 'en', 'Rectangles Circles Buttons Rounded corners in Figma', 'Rectangles Circles Buttons Rounded corners in Figma', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Rectangles,\r\n circles, buttons, and rounded corners are essential elements in UI/UX \r\ndesign. With Figma, you can easily create and customize these elements \r\nto fit your design needs. By using tools such as the properties panel, \r\neffects, and Auto Layout, you can create polished and functional designs\r\n that meet your users\' needs.</p> <p><strong>Rectangles</strong><br>Rectangles\r\n are a basic shape used in UI/UX design to create various elements such \r\nas frames, containers, and backgrounds. In Figma, you can create \r\nrectangles by selecting the rectangle tool and dragging it onto the \r\ncanvas. You can also adjust the size, position, and color of the \r\nrectangle in the properties panel.</p> <p><strong>Circles</strong><br>Circles\r\n are another basic shape used in UI/UX design, commonly used to create \r\nicons, buttons, and avatars. In Figma, you can create circles by \r\nselecting the ellipse tool and dragging it onto the canvas. You can also\r\n adjust the size, position, and color of the circle in the properties \r\npanel.</p> <p><strong>Buttons</strong><br>Buttons are an important \r\nelement in UI/UX design used to trigger actions or navigate to different\r\n pages. In Figma, you can create buttons by combining a rectangle or a \r\ncircle with text. You can also add effects such as shadows or gradients \r\nto give the button a more polished look. Additionally, Figma has a \r\nbuilt-in feature called \"Auto Layout\" that allows you to create buttons \r\nthat adjust their size and layout based on the content inside them.</p> <p><strong>Rounded Corners</strong><br>Rounded\r\n corners are a design element used to soften the edges of shapes, \r\ncreating a more organic and friendly look. In Figma, you can easily \r\nround the corners of rectangles and circles by selecting the shape and \r\nadjusting the corner radius in the properties panel. You can also adjust\r\n the corner radius for each corner individually, giving you more control\r\n over the shape.</p><p><br></p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/SG07wNHyeOw\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p> </div>   </div>'),
(58, 66, 'en', 'How to use color in Figma', 'How to use color in Figma', '<ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Color\r\n is a crucial element of UI/UX design, and using color effectively can \r\ngreatly enhance the visual appeal and usability of your designs. Here \r\nare some tips on how to use color in Figma:</p> <p><strong>Choosing Colors</strong><br>When\r\n choosing colors for your design, it\'s important to consider the \r\nemotions and associations that different colors evoke. For example, blue\r\n is often associated with trust and professionalism, while red can \r\nconvey passion or urgency. Figma offers a range of tools to help you \r\nchoose colors, including a color picker, color swatches, and a color \r\npalette generator.</p> <p><strong>Color Contrast</strong><br>Color \r\ncontrast is an important aspect of accessibility and readability. In \r\nFigma, you can use the built-in contrast checker to ensure that your \r\ncolor choices meet the accessibility standards. You can also adjust the \r\nopacity and blending mode of colors to create different effects and \r\nadjust the contrast.<span></span></p> <p><strong>Gradients</strong><br>Gradients\r\n can be used to add depth and dimension to your designs, and Figma \r\noffers a variety of gradient tools to help you create and customize \r\ngradients. You can choose from linear, radial, or angular gradients, \r\nadjust the colors and opacity of each stop, and add multiple stops to \r\ncreate complex gradients.</p> <p><strong>Color Styles</strong><br>In \r\nFigma, you can create color styles, which are reusable color palettes \r\nthat you can use throughout your design. This can help ensure \r\nconsistency and save time when updating your design. To create a color \r\nstyle, select a color and click the \"Create Style\" button in the \r\nproperties panel.</p> <p><strong>Color Export</strong><br>When exporting\r\n your design, it\'s important to ensure that the colors are accurately \r\nrepresented. Figma allows you to export your design in a variety of \r\nformats, including PNG, SVG, and PDF, and you can choose the color \r\nformat and profile to ensure accurate color representation.</p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/QTvgkvJZ59M\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">  <div class=\"zls-blocks-video zw-pos-re zw-index-none \">   <div class=\"zls-iframe-wrapper zls-video-element\">    </div>    </div></div><br></li></ul><p></p>');
