(82, 90, 'en', 'Layouts', 'Layouts', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Fixed Menu Layouts</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/I2OznwmvwPE\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Grid Systems</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/YH6Wl6ZaIvg\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <p>Use this graphic to complete the exercise below:</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000132013&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000132013\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Responsive Design</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/05mgSw4GkkY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-1yztwzy\">Aspect Ratios</h3> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Most commonly, we’ll be talking about aspect ratios as&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">landscape</em>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">portrait</em>.&nbsp;<strong>Landscape</strong>&nbsp;is when width (in pixels) is greater than the height (like when you hold your phone horizontally).&nbsp;<strong>Portrait</strong>&nbsp;is\r\n the opposite—when the height is greater than the width (like when you \r\nhold your phone vertically). We can also have cases where we’re \r\ndesigning for&nbsp;<strong>squares</strong>&nbsp;(like an Apple Watch), but this is less common.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If you want to dive into this topic further, the&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aspect_ratio\" target=\"_blank\">Wikipedia article on aspect ratios</a>&nbsp;is a solid resource.</p> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-1yztwzy\">Responsive Break Points</h3> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">We need to specify when design layouts change for different screen sizes. We can do this by specifying&nbsp;<strong>Break Points</strong>. These are pixel values where our design will switch to a different layout.</p> <blockquote class=\"css-12m1603\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">A&nbsp;<strong>responsive break point</strong>&nbsp;is a pixel value where the design switches to a different layout.</p> </blockquote> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If you want to learn more about responsive break points, check out&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://ricostacruz.com/til/css-media-query-breakpoints\" target=\"_blank\">this blog post</a>&nbsp;from designer&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://ricostacruz.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rico Sta. Cruz</a>.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">&nbsp;</p> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Grid System in Material-UI</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Material UI</em>&nbsp;design\r\n system has built-in components to help you achieve the layout you\'re \r\nafter. Take a look at the Grid system documentation&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/grid/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p> <blockquote class=\"css-12m1603\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;This\r\n is a technical document for developers. If you\'re not an engineer, \r\ndon\'t worry about the code‚—just focus on the interactive demonstrations\r\n of the components and component properties!</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Sketch Our App\'s Layout</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/-6wSGxFy62U\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">  <div class=\"zls-blocks-video zw-pos-re zw-index-none \">   <div class=\"zls-iframe-wrapper zls-video-element\">    </div>    </div></div><br></li></ul><p></p> </div>   </div>  </div></li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p>'),
(83, 91, 'en', 'Outputs', 'Outputs', '<p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Information In Low-Fidelity</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/YihF6IgvWQE\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Examples of Lo-Fi Information</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/1OGRkEnFtAU\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Output in Material-UI</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The\r\n Material UI design system has built-in components to help you implement\r\n text and outputs. However, keep in mind these examples are&nbsp;<strong>NOT</strong>&nbsp;lo-fi, but quite detailed. You can read in more detail about typography and outputs&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/typography/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p> <blockquote class=\"css-12m1603\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">REMEMBER:\r\n This is a technical document for developers. If you\'re not an engineer,\r\n don\'t worry about the code and focus on the interactive demonstrations \r\nof the components and component properties!</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Sketch Our App\'s Layout</h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/WzxLGpqDqs4\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p></p><p></p></p>'),
(84, 92, 'en', 'Controls', 'Controls', '<p><p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Links</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/YTqR-k_iSHQ\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-1yztwzy\">Links are Fundamental</h3> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Links\r\n may represent one of the most fundamental design controls. They have \r\nexisted since the beginning of what we know as the internet. In fact, \r\nthe first published website was created by CERN in 1991 and can still be\r\n accessed&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"http://info.cern.ch/hypertext/WWW/TheProject.html\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. Even this historic site introduced links to navigate pages.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">When\r\n designing, you\'ll want to tap into someone\'s trained behaviors so you \r\ndon\'t need to teach new skills. With nearly 30 years under its belt, \r\nthe&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">link</em>&nbsp;certainly fits this criteria!</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h1 class=\"chakra-heading css-1ank31f\">&nbsp;</h1> <h1 class=\"chakra-heading css-1ank31f\">&nbsp;</h1> <h1 class=\"chakra-heading css-1ank31f\">Buttons</h1> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Text Buttons</h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/6uUHXobAU0k\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p><br></p></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Icon Buttons</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/xSXDcCvSRiQ\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Using Icon Libraries</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">At\r\n this stage of design, you\'re experimenting. Unless you\'re highly \r\nproficient in graphic arts (I\'m not) it will probably take you a bit of \r\ntime to draw icons to represent your desired actions. Even if you are \r\nhighly proficient, you\'ll often find standardized buttons perform better\r\n for certain actions, since the user will know how to interpret the \r\ngraphic. Thankfully, there are many open-source icon libraries we can \r\nfall back on to download icons as we\'re exploring our interface:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Google Material Icons:&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material.io/resources/icons/\" target=\"_blank\">https://material.io/resources/icons/</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Ion Icons:&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://ionicons.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://ionicons.com/</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Font Awesome:&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://fontawesome.com/icons\" target=\"_blank\">https://fontawesome.com/icons</a></li></ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Controls in Material-UI</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The\r\n Material UI design system has built-in components to help you implement\r\n navigation and controls. You can start by looking at the&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/links/\" target=\"_blank\">link</a>&nbsp;component and then explore the more complex&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/buttons/\" target=\"_blank\">button</a>&nbsp;component.</p> <blockquote class=\"css-12m1603\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">REMEMBER:\r\n This is a technical document for developers. If you\'re not an engineer,\r\n don\'t worry about the code—just focus on the interactive demonstrations\r\n of the components and component properties!</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Controls — Sketch Our App\'s Layout</h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/8pFMwHMuB0M\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p><p></p></p></p>'),
(85, 93, 'en', 'Views', 'Views', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Navigation Stack</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/xSQ7lmmbdGE\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Modals</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/dmu1h_nRJuY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p> </p><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Modals in Material-UI</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The\r\n Material UI design system has built-in components to help you implement\r\n modals. This is one of the more technical pages of the Material-UI \r\nlibrary, but the examples are a great way to demonstrate this design \r\npattern.&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/modal/\" target=\"_blank\">Read about it here</a>.</p> <blockquote class=\"css-12m1603\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">REMEMBER:\r\n This is a technical document for developers. If you\'re not an engineer,\r\n don\'t worry about the code—just focus on the interactive demonstrations\r\n of the components and component properties!</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div>   </div>             <p></p><p></p>'),
(86, 94, 'en', 'Inputs', 'Inputs', '<p><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Ks2mIpC3Oig\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Form Validation</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/pGs5gHoTIVg\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Inputs in Material-UI</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The Material UI design system has built-in components to help you implement inputs. The library includes&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/checkboxes/\" target=\"_blank\">checkboxes</a>,&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/text-fields/\" target=\"_blank\">text-fields</a>, and more complex components like&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/components/pickers/\" target=\"_blank\">Date/Time</a>&nbsp;which we didn\'t discuss. Pay careful attention to the state and how information about form validation is communicated.</p> <blockquote class=\"css-12m1603\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">REMEMBER:\r\n This is a technical document for developers. If you\'re not an engineer,\r\n don\'t worry about the code—just focus on the interactive demonstrations\r\n of the components and component properties!</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\"><span></span>Iterating our Sketches to Include Inputs</h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/92xrMdW-o7Y\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p></p></p>'),
(87, 95, 'en', 'Error Handling', 'Error Handling', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Presenting Actionable Errors</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/k6CNRzE_P8M\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p><p></p>'),
(88, 96, 'en', 'Accessibility: Visual Impairment', 'Accessibility: Visual Impairment', '<p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Visual Acuity</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/AsXwFEs_ZYw\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-1yztwzy\">Facebook\'s Automatic Alt Text</h3> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">In\r\n July 2019, the service that serves user images for Facebook had a \r\nsystem outage—resulting in albums displaying the machine-generated \r\ncaptions in place of the images. This auto-generated alt text is a \r\nfantastic accessibility feature that helps enable visually impaired \r\nusers.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">You can read more about this event&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/7/3/20681231/facebook-outage-image-tags-captions-ai-machine-learning-revealed\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.\r\n Although this may seem like a Sci-Fi feature, machine interpretation of\r\n images has recently become a service you can purchase from companies \r\nlike&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://cloud.google.com/vision/\" target=\"_blank\">Google</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/rekognition/\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">&nbsp;</p> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Color Blindness</h2> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/HYLYDnPUD0U\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p><br></p></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Simulating Colorblindness</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">One\r\n way you can ensure your designs are still interpretable by users \r\naffected by colorblindness is to use a colorblindness filter on your \r\ncomputer.&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://colororacle.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Color Oracle</a>&nbsp;is\r\n a cross-platform (Windows, Mac, Linux) tool that allows you to filter \r\nyour screen to simulate what colors will look like for various forms of \r\ncolor blindness. It\'s a great way to give a quick spot-check to your \r\ndesigns.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">&nbsp;</p> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-1yztwzy\">Additional Reading</h3> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Here are some great additional readings if you want to get deeper into design for users affected by color blindness:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://uxdesign.cc/color-blindness-in-user-interfaces-66c27331b858\" target=\"_blank\">Color blindness: how to design an accessible user interface</a>&nbsp;by Ivan Tuchkov</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/WAI/fundamentals/accessibility-intro/\" target=\"_blank\">Introduction to Web Accessibility</a>&nbsp;from the W3</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/accessible-design-for-users-with-disabilities/\" target=\"_blank\">Accessible Design for Users With Disabilities</a>&nbsp;by Jakob Nielsen</li></ul><p><p></p></p>'),
(89, 97, 'en', 'Accessibility: Hearing Impairment', 'Accessibility: Hearing Impairment', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Closed Captioning</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/FAHakkn64_Y\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p> </p><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-1yztwzy\">Transcribing your Media</h3> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Traditionally,\r\n closed captioning on media was completed by a human who would listen to\r\n the audio track and transcribe, with timecodes to align the audio to \r\nthe text. Although effective, this process was time-consuming and \r\nexpensive. With recent advances in machine learning, we can automate \r\nthis process to receive nearly instantaneous transcriptions at an \r\naffordable price. However, these services can sometimes provide \r\ninaccurate transcription results. Some reliable services include:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/transcribe/\" target=\"_blank\">https://aws.amazon.com/transcribe/</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.rev.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.rev.com/</a></li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://cloud.google.com/speech-to-text/\" target=\"_blank\">https://cloud.google.com/speech-to-text/</a></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div>        <p><br></p><p></p>'),
(90, 98, 'en', 'Accessibility: Limited Dexterity', 'Accessibility: Limited Dexterity', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Button Layout</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/978CHBey0QQ\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\"><br></h2><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Alternative Navigation</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/UKY297ik_rI\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p><p></p><p></p>'),
(91, 99, 'en', 'Lesson Review', 'Lesson Review', '<h1 class=\"chakra-heading css-iuea7g\">Lesson Review</h1><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/JwpNuNacpAY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p> </p><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">What we\'ve learned</h2> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">What&nbsp;<strong>Fidelity</strong>&nbsp;means and how we can communicate the value to stakeholders.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Design networks like&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"http://dribbble.com/\" target=\"_blank\">dribbble</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://behance.net/\" target=\"_blank\">behance</a>&nbsp;where you can grow as a designer.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Common UI Design patterns for&nbsp;<strong>layout, outputs, controls, views, and inputs</strong>&nbsp;and how they might work with coded design libraries like&nbsp;<strong><a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://material-ui.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Material UI</a></strong>.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Qualities and importance of solid&nbsp;<strong>error handling</strong>.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\"><strong>Accessibility principles</strong>&nbsp;to ensure more users are able to use your application comfortably.</li></ul> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">What we\'ll learn next:&nbsp;<strong>Clickable Prototyping</strong></h2> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to improve fidelity by sketching using a dedicated design tool.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to design a user flow for your application.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to transform your sketches into a clickable, interactive design prototype.<span></span></li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div>             <p></p>'),
(92, 100, 'en', 'What is a Clickable Prototype?', 'What is a Clickable Prototype?', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/nq6mNWqfunY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Lesson Overview</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">In this lesson, we\'ll be learning all about clickable prototypes! To be specific, we will look at:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to improve fidelity by sketching using a dedicated design tool.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to design a user flow for your application.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to transform your sketches into a clickable, interactive design prototype.</li></ul><p></p>'),
(93, 101, 'en', 'Getting Started with Figma', 'Getting Started with Figma', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Follow Along with the Videos</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Figma\r\n is a powerful tool that we will use to elevate our designs from \r\nsketches all the way through to a clickable prototype. We strongly \r\nencourage you to follow along with the videos so that you can build your\r\n skills with some hands-on practice (plus, you\'ll want to use Figma for \r\nyour project at the end of this course).</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">&nbsp;</p> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Setup and Basic Layouts</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/UMQzAUQSXwU\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Adding Text</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/r64jrE1dqNU\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Object Properties</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/IJiUbrlUAjU\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p><p></p><p></p> </div>   </div>'),
(94, 102, 'en', 'Design Components', 'Design Components', '<p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Creating a Component</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/vQBcvTs5iX8\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Component Layouts</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/FVCJghnu1t0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h4 class=\"chakra-heading css-xozg3x\">When to use Layout Constraints</h4> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">layout constraints</em>&nbsp;feature\r\n fixes elements relative to the parent. In the context of this video, \r\nthe parent is the component; however, the parent may also be the frame. \r\nThis makes it easy to start to design—and to simulate simple responsive \r\ndesigns directly in Figma—since you\'ll be able to make changes to the \r\nscreen size and notice if there are any design conflicts with the layout\r\n at specific screen sizes.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Component Overrides</h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/766pXqBU4QY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p></p><p></p></p>'),
(95, 103, 'en', 'UI Kits', 'UI Kits', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Finding and Using Figma UI Assets</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/DYof3jo3uyc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">At the time of writing, Figma has moved the assets to&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.figma.com/community/explore\" target=\"_blank\">the community page</a>.</p> You can find the UI Kit used by Gabe&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.figma.com/resources/assets/wireframe-component-library/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&nbsp;and the Material Icons - Rounded&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.figma.com/file/0PZB08VePWE6xT2SYTa6p2/Material-Design-Icons-(Community)?node-id=3%3A8\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.<p></p><p></p>'),
(96, 104, 'en', 'Prototyping with UI Kits', 'Prototyping with UI Kits', '<p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Sketching a Login View</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/FHwH3uzAnQ0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h4 class=\"chakra-heading css-xozg3x\">Why Place Elements Low on the Screen?</h4> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">At\r\n first glance, it may not be obvious why Gabe placed the design elements\r\n towards the bottom of the screen, leaving a lot of whitespace at the \r\ntop. The answer is that phones are getting large and people\'s thumbs \r\ncan\'t reach to the top. This is a design principle made popular by&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://www.samsung.com/us/apps/one-ui/\" target=\"_blank\">Samsung\'s One UI</a>&nbsp;where elements are pushed down on the page so they can be comfortably reached by the user, even on super tall screens.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">&nbsp;</h2> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\"><span></span>Sketching Our Main Views</h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>  <iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/gnkRCV2BsCU\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><p></p></p>'),
(97, 105, 'en', 'Defining Your Flow', 'Defining Your Flow', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Defining Your Flows</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/krWHxqMR1tM\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p><em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The following graphic represents a \r\nuser login flow. Three actions are labeled A, B, and C. Use this graphic\r\n to answer the question below.</em></p><p></p>'),
(98, 106, 'en', 'Clickable Prototypes', 'Clickable Prototypes', '<p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Creating Login&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">View States</em></h2> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">On this page, we\'ll be creating some&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">view states</em>. A&nbsp;<strong>view state</strong>&nbsp;is\r\n a representation of a screen with a certain configuration or user \r\ninteraction. For example, a user may have entered text or hovered over a\r\n specific element; each of these actions would need to be represented as\r\n a different&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">view state</em>.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">In\r\n Figma, we\'ll need to create a frame and change the frame with whatever \r\ninformation is relevant for that state. To keep things consistent, it\'s \r\nusually a good idea to use components to represent the overall view and \r\nthen override the component for each view state.</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/wgDBM_W20RE\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Wiring Your Interactions</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/K5fBPuG9ry4\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>'),
(99, 107, 'en', 'Design Handoff', 'Design Handoff', '<ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Throughout\r\n the design process, you\'ll often find yourself needing to share your \r\ndesigns with different stakeholders. You may be seeking feedback or \r\napproval from stakeholders, or your engineering team might need a \r\nreference so they know what they\'re implementing. So let\'s looks at some\r\n of the different ways to share a Figma design.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Share the Figma Link</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">You can share the design itself by simply sending a link to your design file. It\'s as easy as clicking&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">share</em>, setting the link-sharing permissions (<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">can view</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">can edit</code>)\r\n and copying the link. You can then paste this link into whatever tools \r\nyou use to communicate (email, Slack, teams) and the recipient can view \r\nthe contents.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Keep in mind, this link is live. That means as you edit the design, the recipient of this link will see those changes.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000133411&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000133411\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Export as Images</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If\r\n you\'re looking to simply share one or more screens in a fixed way \r\n(something you won\'t change as you continue working), you might want to \r\nexport your screens as images.</p> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">You can do this by simply clicking on the element (<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">frame</em>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<em class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">shape</em>)\r\n and using the export tools in the right sidebar. This will produce a \r\ngraphic that you can send to a stakeholder for their review without them\r\n needing to navigate or browse through the entire design.</p> </div>   </div>   </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">    <div class=\"zls-blocks-image zw-txt-al-c\">  <img alt=\"images\" src=\"https://download.zoho.com/webdownload?x-service=ZohoLearn&amp;event-id=6352450000000132017&amp;x-cli-msg=%7B%22scopeID%22%3A%226352450000000004002%22%2C%22attachmentItemType%22%3A%22LESSON%22%2C%22isInline%22%3A%22true%22%2C%22courseId%22%3A%226352450000000008045%22%7D\" id=\"6352450000000132017\" style=\"min-height:\'100px\'\">  </div>     </div> </li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"> <div class=\"css-u8svcc\"> <div class=\"copy-length css-0\"> <div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Design to Code with Spec Sheets</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">The\r\n most advanced sharing use-case is sharing with engineers. Developers \r\nmight need more information (colors, spacing, sizes) while implementing \r\nyour design. By sharing a link with&nbsp;<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">can view</code>&nbsp;permissions, engineers can view properties for each element so they don\'t need to reach out to you with simple questions.</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/sSe8zIZEAKQ\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p> </div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></li></ul><p></p>'),
(100, 108, 'en', 'Lesson Review', 'Lesson Review', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/NQWycboDWoc\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><div class=\"zls-container zw-flex zw-flex-column zw-fl-grow zw-p-all30 zls-overflow-auto zw-pos-re zls-block-type\">      <ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\"><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">  <div class=\"zls-blocks-video zw-pos-re zw-index-none \">   <div class=\"zls-iframe-wrapper zls-video-element\">    </div>    </div> </div> <br></li><li class=\"\" style=\"padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\"> <div class=\"zls-blocks-container\">   <div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">What we\'ve learned</h2> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How we can improve our designs using&nbsp;<strong>Figma</strong>, a dedicated design tool.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Figma fundamentals including&nbsp;<strong>Shapes, Layouts, Properties, and Groups</strong>.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How we can remain organized using reusable&nbsp;<strong>Components</strong>.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Using published components in&nbsp;<strong>UI Kits</strong>&nbsp;to design quickly and effectively.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">An effective way to define&nbsp;<strong>User flows</strong>&nbsp;to ensure we\'ve designed a complete experience.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Translating designs into an interactive, clickable&nbsp;<strong>Feels-Like Prototype</strong>.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">Basics of communicating Figma to engineers for&nbsp;<strong>Design Handoff</strong>.</li></ul> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">What we\'ll learn next:&nbsp;<strong>Usability Testing</strong></h2> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to design a study to identify problems with your design.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to run the study with real respondents.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to iterate your design to fix issues.</li></ul> </div>   </div>   </div> </li></ul>     </div>       <p></p>'),
(101, 109, 'en', 'Why Usability Test?', 'Why Usability Test?', '<h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Getting Ready to Be Wrong</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/X1AAzm3MdNk\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>  </p><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\">   <div class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \"> <h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Lesson Overview</h2> <p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">In this lesson, we\'ll be looking at:</p> <ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to design a study to identify problems with your design.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to run the study with real respondents.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to iterate your design to fix issues.</li></ul> </div>   </div>  <p></p>'),
(102, 110, 'en', 'Styles of Usability Studies', 'Styles of Usability Studies', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/g8ldN4VpePg\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><p>In the video, we mentioned that un-moderated studies are almost always \r\nremote, and are conducted with specialized tools where you can have many\r\n users accomplish a task in parallel.&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://usertesting.com/\" target=\"_blank\">UserTesting.com</a>&nbsp;is a good example of a specialized service that helps you run un-moderated, remote sessions.</p>'),
(103, 111, 'en', 'Moderating a Usability Session', 'Moderating a Usability Session', '<p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Parts of a Moderated Usability Session</h2> Before watching the video below, download the usability guide so you can follow along:&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1NUrRbhKBtckPvxnXGjuZq0t_uWjPizWaxUwn1ghEWWY/copy\" target=\"_blank\">Google Doc</a>,&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"http://udacity.github.io/UXND/lofi/UsabilityGuide-UdacityAir.docx\" target=\"_blank\">docx</a>,&nbsp;<a class=\"chakra-link css-otuu82\" href=\"http://udacity.github.io/UXND/lofi/UsabilityGuide-UdacityAir.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">pdf</a></p><p><br></p><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\">Defining Tasks</h2><p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/kocTJKGss-4\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe><br></p><p><p></p></p>');
