ction: ltr;\"><code class=\" language-jsx\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; color: black; background: linear-gradient(transparent 50%, rgba(69, 142, 209, 0.04) 50%) 0% 0% / 3em 3em local content-box content-box rgb(253, 253, 253); font-family: Consolas, Monaco, &quot;Andale Mono&quot;, &quot;Ubuntu Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; max-height: inherit; height: inherit; padding: 0px 1em; display: block; overflow: auto; text-shadow: white 0px 1px; direction: ltr; box-shadow: rgb(53, 140, 203) -1px 0px 0px 0px, rgb(223, 223, 223) 0px 0px 0px 1px; position: relative; border-left: 10px solid rgb(53, 140, 203);\">{\r\n    count: 3,\r\n    games: [3,5,7]\r\n}\r\n</code></pre><div class=\"buttonGroup__atx\">&nbsp;</div></div></div></li></ul><h3 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Level 4<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_04/tasks#level-4\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">​</a></h3><p>Write a function&nbsp;<code>goat_awards</code>&nbsp;that takes 1 parameter:&nbsp;<code>csv_file</code>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<code>csv_file</code>&nbsp;is the name of csv file containing data.</p><p>The function primarily reads the csv file and:</p><ul><li>Finds out who scored the most points of all the players</li><li>Finds out who recorded the most assists of all the players</li><li>Finds out who recoreded the most rebounds of all the players:</li><li>Finds out who recoreded the most blocks of all the players:</li></ul><p>It should return a dictionary like this:</p><div class=\"language-jsx codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block\"><div class=\"codeBlockContent_biex\"><pre class=\"prism-code codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar  language-jsx\" style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: 1.5; color: black; background: rgb(245, 242, 240); font-family: Consolas, Monaco, &quot;Andale Mono&quot;, &quot;Ubuntu Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; padding: 1em; text-shadow: white 0px 1px; direction: ltr;\"><code class=\" language-jsx\" style=\"line-height: 1.5; color: black; background: linear-gradient(transparent 50%, rgba(69, 142, 209, 0.04) 50%) 0% 0% / 3em 3em local content-box content-box rgb(253, 253, 253); font-family: Consolas, Monaco, &quot;Andale Mono&quot;, &quot;Ubuntu Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; max-height: inherit; height: inherit; padding: 0px 1em; display: block; overflow: auto; text-shadow: white 0px 1px; direction: ltr; box-shadow: rgb(53, 140, 203) -1px 0px 0px 0px, rgb(223, 223, 223) 0px 0px 0px 1px; position: relative; border-left: 10px solid rgb(53, 140, 203);\">{\r\n    most_points: [\'Lex Lu\',356],\r\n    most_assists: [\'Lex Lu\',356],\r\n    most_reboundss: [\'Lex Lu\',356],\r\n    most_blocks: [\'Lex Lu\',356]\r\n}</code></pre></div></div></div></div><div class=\"zls-learner-answer-con zw-m-t40\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b10 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 10px;\">Email your submission to your instructor</div></div>'),
(125, 133, 'en', 'Assignment 4', 'Assignment 4', '<p><div class=\"zls-learner-answer-con zw-m-t40\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"></div></p><div class=\"zls-header-con zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem;\"><h1>React Coding Tasks</h1><p style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">You have at most 48 hours to complete the following challenges.</p><h2 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Fantasy Football XI<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_05/tasks#fantasy-football-xi\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px; color: var(--product-accent-color);\">​</a></h2><p style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">create a fantasy fooballer\'s list application using function-based components and the&nbsp;<code>useState</code>&nbsp;hook.</p><h3 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Requirements:<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_05/tasks#requirements\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px; color: var(--product-accent-color);\">​</a></h3><ol><li>Create a component called \"FantasyList\" that renders a form with a text input for the player name, dropdown list of positions and a submit button.</li><li>When the form is submitted, use the&nbsp;<code>useState</code>&nbsp;hook to add the inputted footballer to an array of footballers.</li><li>Display the list of footballers in the component, each footballer should have a button to delete the player.</li><li>Add a button to clear all the footballers from the list.</li><li>Style the application using CSS.</li></ol><p style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">This assignment will help you practice using function-based components, forms and events, state, and basic styling in React.</p></div></div>');
INSERT INTO `text_lesson_translations` (`id`, `text_lesson_id`, `locale`, `title`, `summary`, `content`) VALUES
(126, 134, 'en', 'Assignment 5', 'Assignment 5', '<div class=\"zls-header-con zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\"><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem;\"><h1>Django Coding Tasks</h1><p>You have at most 72 hours to complete the following challenge.</p><h2 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Fantasy Football XI API<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_06/tasks#fantasy-football-xi-api\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">​</a></h2><p>Create a fantasy fooballer\'s API application using DRF.</p><h3 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Requirements<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_06/tasks#requirements\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">​</a></h3><h4 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Level 1<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_06/tasks#level-1\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">​</a></h4><ol><li><p>Create two models&nbsp;<code>Footballer</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code>Club</code>.</p><p><code>Footballer</code>&nbsp;should have a first name, nick name, last name, date of birth, position, number, value and club.</p><p>The&nbsp;<code>Club</code>&nbsp;should have name, country and division.</p></li><li><p>Create&nbsp;<code>views</code>&nbsp;for both models that perform&nbsp;<strong>CRUD</strong>&nbsp;operations i.e&nbsp;<strong>C</strong>reate,&nbsp;<strong>R</strong>ead,&nbsp;<strong>U</strong>pdate,&nbsp;<strong>D</strong>elete.</p></li><li><p>Make the&nbsp;<code>urls</code>&nbsp;for the views you created.</p></li></ol><h4 class=\"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7\">Level 2<a href=\"https://pms-node.web.app/docs/module_06/tasks#level-2\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">​</a></h4><ol><li><em>(OPTIONAL)</em>&nbsp;Add documentation using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drf-spectacular.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">drf spectacular</a></li></ol><p>This assignment will help you practice implementing a simple API using DRF, and additionally, adding documentation.</p></div></div><div class=\"zls-learner-answer-con zw-m-t40\" style=\"margin-top: 40px;\"><div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b10 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 10px;\">Your Submission</div><div class=\"zls-mce-customize-toolbar zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; border: 2px solid rgb(234, 234, 234); background: var(--white); border-radius: 5px;\"><div id=\"textLessonToolbarLearnerAnswer\" class=\"zls-mce-toolbar\" style=\"padding: 6px; border-radius: 0px; background: transparent; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(234, 234, 234);\"><div id=\"mceu_373\" class=\"mce-tinymce mce-tinymce-inline mce-container mce-panel\" hidefocus=\"1\" tabindex=\"-1\" role=\"application\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px none; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background: transparent; color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-family: Lato, Arial, sans-serif; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: relative; width: 935.333px; height: 64px; text-wrap: nowrap; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none; box-shadow: none; left: 0px; top: 0px; visibility: inherit !important;\"><div id=\"mceu_373-body\" class=\"mce-container-body mce-abs-layout\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background: transparent; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: relative; width: 935.333px; height: 64px; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none; overflow: hidden;\"><div id=\"mceu_373-absend\" class=\"mce-abs-end\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: static; width: 0px; height: 0px; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none;\"></div><div id=\"mceu_374\" class=\"mce-toolbar-grp mce-container mce-panel mce-abs-layout-item mce-first mce-last\" hidefocus=\"1\" tabindex=\"-1\" role=\"group\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: none; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: static; width: 935.333px; height: 64px; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none; left: 0px; top: 0px;\"><div id=\"mceu_374-body\" class=\"mce-container-body mce-stack-layout\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background: transparent; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: static; width: 935.333px; height: 64px; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none;\"><div id=\"mceu_375\" class=\"mce-container mce-toolbar mce-stack-layout-item mce-first mce-last\" role=\"toolbar\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background: transparent; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: static; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none; width: auto !important; height: auto !important;\"><div id=\"mceu_375-body\" class=\"mce-container-body mce-flow-layout\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background: transparent; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: static; text-wrap: wrap; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none; width: auto !important; height: auto !important;\"><div id=\"mceu_376\" class=\"mce-container mce-flow-layout-item mce-first mce-btn-group\" role=\"group\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; background: transparent; text-shadow: none; float: none; position: static; text-wrap: nowrap; cursor: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: normal; box-sizing: content-box; direction: ltr; max-width: none; display: inline-block; width: auto !important; height: auto !important;\"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>'),
(127, 135, 'en', 'Write Your Interview Questions', 'Write Your Interview Questions', '<div class=\"zls-header-con zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\"><div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px;\"><div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px; font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Question</div><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;\"><p>Complete the following tasks and upload the document:</p><p>- Write your interview questions</p><p>- Check that your interview is clearly related to one of your research questions</p><p>- Write a rationale explaining why each question is relevant and should be included</p><p>- Write questions and accompanying rationales to your reach plan document</p><p><br></p><p>For submission, Email the document to your instructor.</p></div></div></div>'),
(128, 136, 'en', 'Time to Sketch Again', 'Time to Sketch Again', '<div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px; font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Question</div><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif;\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Having run your user interviews and surveys, hopefully by now you have a better idea of your user\'s needs and what you want to design to meet those needs. As part of your final project, your goal is to sketch out at least one screen of the potential core experience for your use.</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">What are some of the interesting findings from your research project? You should incorporate at least one of these findings in your sketch.</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Remember, don\'t be intimidated by sketching! This should be a fun and creative way to generate ideas—and you should not feel like it has to be perfect. You can (and should) iterate on your design anyway. (Focus on improvement over time, not perfection!)</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">For this exercise, you can choose to draw a single screen or multiple screens. You can sketch on paper or on a tablet, whichever you prefer.</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">&nbsp;</p><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Have fun sketching!</p></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><strong>Sketch one or more screens</strong>&nbsp;for the product you\'re designing.</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">When sketching,&nbsp;<strong>make use of at least one of the findings from your research</strong>.</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\"><strong>Take a photo</strong>&nbsp;(or screenshot) of the design and copy it into a word document or slide (so that you can add text next to it). You can use whatever app you like for this part, as long as you can export the result as a PDF (this is how you\'ll submit it later on).</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Next to your design, explain what this screen is about and what users are supposed to do on this screen.</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Also, explain which research finding(s) you applied and describe how they make the user experience better.</li></ul></div></div></div>'),
(129, 137, 'en', 'Emotional Design Exercise', 'Emotional Design Exercise', '<div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px; font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Question</div><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif;\"><p><img src=\"https://internship.rightclicksolutions.com.ng/_lms/api/portal/right-click-academy/course/6352450000000008045/lesson/6352450000000037945/file/6352450000000037955\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width: 100%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"></p><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Your mission is to make the existing design (above) better. How would you use emotional design to encourage users?</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">This is intended as fun sketching exercise. Be creative!</p><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">There is no single correct solution, but it\'s always a good idea to get feedback on your designs to see how people react. So, once you\'re done sketching, consider sharing the design with a friend or fellow student to see how they react.</p></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Have a try at improving the emotional design of the VocabBuilder screen</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">If you like, share your improved design with someone else to see how they react</li></ul></div></div></div>'),
(130, 138, 'en', 'Sketch Your Design', 'Sketch Your Design', '<p></p><div class=\"zls-learner-answer-con zw-m-t40\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"></div><p></p><div class=\"zls-header-con zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem;\"><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\"><div class=\"copy-length css-0\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><div><h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-knkq03\">Sketch your design</h3></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p><strong>Sketch at least one screen</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>for your product, using pen and paper (or a tablet, if you prefer).</p><p>In your sketch,<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>use at least one design principle</strong><span><span>&nbsp;</span>to improve the user experience.</span></p><p><strong>Take a photo</strong><span><span>&nbsp;</span>(or screenshot) of the design and copy it into a word document or slide (so that you can add text next to it).<br></span></p><p>Next to your design,&nbsp;<strong>explain what this screen is about and what users are supposed to do</strong><span><span>&nbsp;</span>on this screen.</span></p><p>Also, next to your design, explain which&nbsp;<strong>design principle(s)</strong><span>&nbsp;you applied and describe how they improved the design.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>'),
(131, 139, 'en', 'Design Practice', 'Design Practice', '<div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px; font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Question</div><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif;\"><p>Redesign a website or app you frequently use and apply the concepts they\'ve learned, such as using frames or groups to organize elements, using color effectively, and editing objects.</p><p>Instructions:</p><p>- Share the name of the app or website you are redesigning</p><p>- Design a MAXIMUM of 3 screens using figma</p><p>- Submit the link to your figma file via email</p></div>'),
(132, 140, 'en', 'Design Practice 2', 'Design Practice 2', '<p style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Using your knowledge from the previous Figma Essentials lessons, design 3 screens of a simple food ordering application&nbsp;</p><p style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Your design should capture:</p><ol style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li>Food menu/list screen</li><li>Single Food Selection Screen</li><li>Checkout Screen</li></ol><p style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Submit the link to your Figma file and make sure it is visible to anyone with the link.</p>'),
(133, 141, 'en', 'Design Assignment', 'Design Assignment', '<p style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Design a web page (2 screens) for a fictional car rental company. The web page should include the following principles that were taught during the mentorship session:</p><p>Columns and Grids</p><p>Components and Instances</p><p>Variants and Variables</p><p>Prototyping</p><p>Libraries</p><p>Animation and Micro Interactions</p>'),
(134, 142, 'en', 'Set Up Your Miro Board', 'Set Up Your Miro Board', '<div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px;\">Question</div><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem;\"><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\" style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\"><div class=\"css-1do9afp\"><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-knkq03\">Set Up Your Miro Board</h3><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Follow these steps to set up a miro board which we\'ll use throughout the course!</p></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ol><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Navigate to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://miro.com/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px;\">Miro.com</a></li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Sign up for a new account—or log in if you have an account</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">You may need to create a team to get started—you can just create one with whatever name you like</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Create a new board and give it a title (it may also create one for your automatically when you sign up, which is fine)</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Create a frame and add some post-it notes on the board</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Click the&nbsp;<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">Share</code>&nbsp;button copy the Board Link</li></ol><p>After following the steps above, submit the Board link via email to your instructor</p><div><br></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\" style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\"><div class=\"css-17mjet2\"></div></div></div></div>'),
(135, 143, 'en', 'Miro Practice', 'Miro Practice', '<p><div class=\"zls-learner-answer-con zw-m-t40\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"></div></p><div class=\"zls-header-con zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"zls-f-w600 zw-m-b5 zw-primary-txt-color\" style=\"font-weight: 600; color: var(--product-accent-color); margin-bottom: 5px;\">Question</div><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem;\"><div class=\"css-1aq2jbx\"><div class=\"chakra-container css-1es7f9a\"><div class=\"css-0\"><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\"><div class=\"css-1do9afp\"><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\" style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">Try it yourself! Rewatch the video in the previous lesson and try using the active listening technique to write down some observation notes.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Open your Miro board and create a frame for practice</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Create a few blank note cards</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Your notes should be short with large text</li><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Your notes should contain enough detail that they are understandable on their own</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>'),
(136, 144, 'en', 'Exercise', 'Exercise', '<p><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\" style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\"><div class=\"copy-length css-0\"></div></div></div></p><div class=\"css-1m96lhp\" style=\"color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"css-u8svcc\"><div class=\"css-1do9afp\"><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\" style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">Try the Affinity Mapping Technique in Miro using the travel study data we\'ve provided.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\" style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">Download the sample data by clicking this link:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://udacity.github.io/UXND/lofi/sample_travel_data.csv\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"outline: 0px; color: var(--product-accent-color);\">https://udacity.github.io/UXND/lofi/sample_travel_data.csv</a></p></div><br><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Copy the data in the CSV file</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Open your Miro Board created in Lesson 1</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Click the Note tool in the left side panel or press&nbsp;<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">N</code>&nbsp;on your keyboard</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Click&nbsp;<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">Bulk Mode</code></li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Paste the Data</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Cluster the information by moving the notes based on the criteria in the concept video</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Name your clusters using the text tool</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div>'),
(137, 145, 'en', 'Exercise', 'Exercise', '<p><div class=\"zls-learner-answer-con zw-m-t40\" style=\"margin-top: 40px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"></div></p><div class=\"zls-header-con zw-m-b20\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"zls-fs16\" style=\"font-size: 1.6rem;\"><div class=\"css-k008qs\"><div><h3 class=\"chakra-heading css-knkq03\">Try It Yourself!</h3><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\" style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">Try using these techniques to ideate solutions for our design prompt:&nbsp;<code class=\"chakra-code css-p3l7io\">How Might We provide more relevant information about trip status to frequent travelers so they can experience less frustration during their trip?</code></p></div></div></div><div class=\"chakra-stack css-1ac1sc7\"><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Open your Miro board with the Air Travel Synthesis from the last concept</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Pick an area of design exploration (try to focus on one or two themes)</li></ul></div><div class=\"ureact-markdown css-tc5hjw\"><ul><li class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\">Use one or more technique from this lesson to identify at least 10 ideas for how you might solve the problem</li></ul><p><br>Send your submission as an email attachment to your instructor.</p></div></div></div></div>'),
(138, 146, 'en', 'What is a Clickable Prototype?', 'What is a Clickable Prototype?', '<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/nq6mNWqfunY\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" class=\"note-video-clip\"></iframe></p><ul class=\"zls-ul-reset zls-blocks-wrapper zw-fl-grow\" purpose=\"blockSortableContainer\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; flex-grow: 1; color: rgb(36, 42, 66); font-family: LatoLatin, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><li purpose=\"zw-block-idx-1\" class=\"\" style=\"padding: 20px;\"><div class=\"zls-blocks-container\" zls-lms-purpose=\"zls-blocks-container\" style=\"max-width: 950px; width: 950px; margin: 0px auto;\"><lms-block-text columns=\"1\" background=\"\" lyte-rendered=\"\"><div class=\"zls-blocks zls-fixed-width:950 zls-fs17 zw-word-wrap zls-grid zls-gap20 zls-g-col1\" purpose=\"zls-editor-block\" style=\"font-size: 1.7rem; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere; display: grid; gap: 20px; max-width: 950px; width: 950px; margin: 0px auto;\"><div lmsblockeditindex=\"0\" class=\"zls-tinymce-text-content \" data-placeholder=\"Good products come from good craftsmanship. They come from careful attention to design, from endless rounds of refinement, and iteration. But none of those things come easily.                       \" purpose=\"block-text-1-0\" focus=\"lms-block-text => inputTextOnFocus(this,event,index)\" style=\"min-height: 20px; font-size: 1.7rem; line-height: 1.6; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere;\"><h2 class=\"chakra-heading css-lb1dt4\" style=\"margin: 5px 0px;\">Lesson Overview</h2><p class=\"chakra-text css-o3oz8b\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 1.7rem; line-height: 1.6; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere;\">In this lesson, we\'ll be learning all about clickable prototypes! To be specific, we will look at:</p><ul class=\"css-19qh3zo\"><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to improve fidelity by sketching using a dedicated design tool.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to design a user flow for your application.</li><li class=\"css-cvpopp\">How to transform your sketches into a clickable, interactive design prototype.</li></ul></div></div></lms-block-text></div></li></ul>'),
(139, 147, 'en', 'Assignment 6', 'Assignment 6', '<ol>\r\n<li>Implement a function to determine if a string has all unique characters. You<br>cannot use additional data structures except in built JS data structures.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Implement a function to perform basic string compression using the counts<br>of repeated characters. For example, the string aabcccccaaa would become a2blc5a3. If the<br>\"compressed\" string would not become smaller than the original string, your method should return<br>the original string. You can assume the string has only uppercase and lowercase letters (a - z).<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Write a program that reads students’ names followed by their test<br>scores. The program should output each student’s name followed by the<br>test scores and the relevant grade. It should also find and print the high-<br>est test score and the name of the students having the highest test score.<br>Student data should be stored in an object variable of type studentType,<br>which has four components: <br><br>studentFName of type string<br>studentLName of type string<br>testScore of type int (testScore is between 0 and 100) and<br>grade of type char.<br><br>Suppose that the class has 20 students. Use an array of 20 components of type studentType.<br>Your program must contain at least the following functions:<br><br>a.) A function to read the students’ data into the array.<br>b.) A function to assign the relevant grade to each student.<br>c.) A function to find the highest test score.<br>d.) A function to print the names of the students having the highest test score.<br><br>Your program must output each student’s name in this form: <br><br>- last name followed by a comma, followed by a space, followed by the first name;<br>the name must be left justified. <br><br>Moreover, other than declaring the variables, the js file should only be a collection of function calls.</li></ol>');
