(3, 3, 'en', 'Natural Gas Trading and Risk Management', 'This course explores the intricacies of natural gas trading and risk management in the energy industry. Participants will gain an understanding of natural gas markets, pricing mechanisms, and trading strategies. The course covers topics such as physical and financial trading, risk assessment, hedging techniques, and portfolio management. Through simulations and real-world case studies, participants will develop the skills necessary to make informed decisions and manage risks in natural gas trading activities.', '<p>This course explores the intricacies of natural gas trading and risk management in the energy industry. Participants will gain an understanding of natural gas markets, pricing mechanisms, and trading strategies. The course covers topics such as physical and financial trading, risk assessment, hedging techniques, and portfolio management. Through simulations and real-world case studies, participants will develop the skills necessary to make informed decisions and manage risks in natural gas trading activities.</p>'),
(4, 4, 'en', 'Offshore Decommissioning and Abandonment', 'This course focuses on the decommissioning and abandonment of offshore oil and gas facilities. Participants will learn about the regulatory requirements, technical challenges, and project management considerations associated with the cessation of production and the removal of offshore platforms and pipelines. The course covers topics such as plug and abandonment techniques, environmental impact assessments, and decommissioning cost estimation. Case studies and industry best practices will be explored to provide participants with practical knowledge in offshore decommissioning.', '<p>This course focuses on the decommissioning and abandonment of offshore oil and gas facilities. Participants will learn about the regulatory requirements, technical challenges, and project management considerations associated with the cessation of production and the removal of offshore platforms and pipelines. The course covers topics such as plug and abandonment techniques, environmental impact assessments, and decommissioning cost estimation. Case studies and industry best practices will be explored to provide participants with practical knowledge in offshore decommissioning.</p>'),
(5, 5, 'en', 'Petroleum Refining Fundamentals', 'This course provides a comprehensive understanding of the key processes and operations involved in petroleum refining. Participants will learn about crude oil distillation, catalytic cracking, hydroprocessing, and product blending. The course covers topics such as refinery configuration, product quality specifications, and environmental considerations in refining operations. Through case studies and interactive discussions, participants will gain practical insights into refinery operations and optimization strategies.', '<p>This course provides a comprehensive understanding of the key processes and operations involved in petroleum refining. Participants will learn about crude oil distillation, catalytic cracking, hydroprocessing, and product blending. The course covers topics such as refinery configuration, product quality specifications, and environmental considerations in refining operations. Through case studies and interactive discussions, participants will gain practical insights into refinery operations and optimization strategies.</p>');
